# NOTICE

PaperTap is based on a chain of forks of the original NFC E-Ink Writer project.

## Fork History

**PaperTap** (Current Project)
- Author: Rob Berwick
- Copyright: (c) 2025 Rob Berwick
- Changes: Rebranded to PaperTap, added PDF URL sharing, QR code auto-detection, 
  settings screen, audio feedback, Material Design 3 UI updates, removed dithering 
  in favor of threshold-based processing for optimal QR code clarity

**NFC E-Paper Writer** (harinworks fork)
- Repository: https://github.com/harinworks/nfc-epaper-writer
- Author: harinworks
- Copyright: (c) 2024 harinworks
- Changes: PDF support, QR code extraction with ML Kit, image processing improvements

**NFC E-Paper Writer** (mk-fg fork)
- Repository: https://github.com/mk-fg/nfc-epaper-writer
- Author: mk-fg
- Copyright: (c) 2024 mk-fg
- Changes: Build fixes, UI improvements

**NFC E-Ink Writer** (Original Project)
- Repository: https://github.com/joshuatz/nfc-epaper-writer
- Author: Joshua Tzucker
- Copyright: (c) 2021 Joshua Tzucker
- Original implementation with WaveShare SDK integration

All versions are licensed under the MIT License.
See the LICENSE file for the complete license text.

## Third-Party Components

This software also includes or depends on the following third-party components:

### WaveShare Android SDK
- Used for NFC communication with e-paper displays
- Copyright: WaveShare Electronics
- Documentation: https://www.waveshare.com/wiki/Android_SDK_for_NFC-Powered_e-Paper

### ML Kit Barcode Scanning
- Library: com.google.mlkit:barcode-scanning:17.3.0
- Copyright: Google LLC
- License: Apache License 2.0

